WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.803 --> 00:00:14.014
[driver. on radio] Inbound
with two tons of bauxite.

2
00:00:18.060 --> 00:00:19.977
[machines whirring]

3
00:00:19.978 --> 00:00:22.021
[cosmonaut. in Russian]
You couldn't be more wrong.

4
00:00:22.022 --> 00:00:24.941
It is a return to the
ideals of Lenin and Stalin.

5
00:00:24.942 --> 00:00:26.734
Oh. please.

6
00:00:26.735 --> 00:00:30.029
I came here to test the
modified anchor clamps.

7
00:00:30.030 --> 00:00:31.990
not discuss geopolitics.

8
00:00:32.698 --> 00:00:34.951
I already tested the clamps.

9
00:00:34.952 --> 00:00:36.036
They work fine.

10
00:00:37.037 --> 00:00:39.581
If only your opinion were
enough for Star City.

11
00:00:40.290 --> 00:00:41.291
Let's go!

12
00:00:44.127 --> 00:00:48.464
[cosmonaut] You don't have Gorbachev
and his cronies to protect you anymore.

13
00:00:48.465 --> 00:00:50.633
New times. Svetlana Zakharova.

14
00:00:50.634 --> 00:00:51.884
Oh. yes.

15
00:00:51.885 --> 00:00:54.554
Will Korzhenko save us
the same way Stalin did?

16
00:00:54.555 --> 00:00:56.305
Shooting dissidents
in the forest

17
00:00:56.306 --> 00:00:57.723
and dumping their
bodies in pits?

18
00:00:57.724 --> 00:01:00.852
[cosmonaut] Stalin won
the Great Patriotic War.

19
00:01:00.853 --> 00:01:03.521
[Svetlana] The blood of an
entire generation won that war.

20
00:01:03.522 --> 00:01:04.438
Not Stalin.

21
00:01:04.439 --> 00:01:06.941
Listen. the West walked
all over Mother Russia!

22
00:01:06.942 --> 00:01:09.235
Korzhenko will return
us to the days when

23
00:01:09.236 --> 00:01:11.863
the world lived in
fear of our might.

24
00:01:11.864 --> 00:01:13.907
You are delusional. Vasily.

25
00:01:14.825 --> 00:01:16.659
And you are a traitor.

26
00:01:16.660 --> 00:01:18.244
Spitting on your own culture

27
00:01:18.245 --> 00:01:20.288
spreading your legs
in front of the West.

28
00:01:20.289 --> 00:01:21.956
Go to hell.

29
00:01:21.957 --> 00:01:23.458
Go yourself.

30
00:01:24.293 --> 00:01:25.501
This is complete bullshit!

31
00:01:25.502 --> 00:01:27.004
[Vasily speaks Russian]

32
00:01:27.963 --> 00:01:30.632
[both grunting]

33
00:01:31.258 --> 00:01:35.803
- [Vasily grunting]
- [suit hisses]

34
00:01:35.804 --> 00:01:38.682
[Vasily wheezes. pants]

35
00:01:40.559 --> 00:01:42.226
Exhale or your lungs will burst!

36
00:01:42.227 --> 00:01:43.896
[wheezing]

37
00:01:46.315 --> 00:01:51.820
[in English] Mayday. Mayday! Happy Valley.
we need a medevac at Depo One ASAP!

38
00:04:00.866 --> 00:04:03.452
[Russian chatter]

39
00:04:12.002 --> 00:04:13.461
and may never regain
consciousness.

40
00:04:13.462 --> 00:04:15.171
I have spoken to
President Korzhenko

41
00:04:15.172 --> 00:04:18.216
and he demands that
there be repercussions.

42
00:04:31.271 --> 00:04:32.606
[in English] Jesus Christ.

43
00:04:34.316 --> 00:04:35.942
What did Mayakovsky say?

44
00:04:35.943 --> 00:04:40.030
Uh. Vasily's still unconscious.
Got a hell of a case of the bends.

45
00:04:41.198 --> 00:04:45.201
Won't be out of the hyperbaric
chambers for another few days minimum.

46
00:04:45.202 --> 00:04:48.162
And that's when they'll know if
there's any long-term damage.

47
00:04:48.163 --> 00:04:50.706
Been seeing more of this up
here in the last couple of weeks

48
00:04:50.707 --> 00:04:52.000
since what happened in Moscow.

49
00:04:52.668 --> 00:04:54.253
Russian against Russian.

50
00:04:55.295 --> 00:04:57.631
We can't have this.
Ed. Not up here.

51
00:04:59.466 --> 00:05:00.843
[groans] What are you saying?

52
00:05:01.343 --> 00:05:02.635
I'm pulling her wings.

53
00:05:02.636 --> 00:05:05.471
[scoffs] Just because he lost the
fight doesn't mean he was innocent.

54
00:05:05.472 --> 00:05:07.557
Svetlana could
have killed Galkin.

55
00:05:07.558 --> 00:05:09.141
But she didn't.

56
00:05:09.142 --> 00:05:12.478
Either way. I'm removing her
from flight status indefinitely.

57
00:05:12.479 --> 00:05:14.981
Come on. Dani. You know
what flying means to her.

58
00:05:14.982 --> 00:05:19.068
Yes. But there have got to be
consequences for what she did.

59
00:05:19.069 --> 00:05:22.613
She'll be confined to the
base without pay for 60 sols.

60
00:05:22.614 --> 00:05:24.699
I think you should reconsider.

61
00:05:24.700 --> 00:05:27.743
You said it yourself. Look. she's
one of the best pilots we got.

62
00:05:27.744 --> 00:05:30.872
And if you wanna stay on the
asteroid training mission schedule.

63
00:05:30.873 --> 00:05:32.039
we'll have a hell of a time

64
00:05:32.040 --> 00:05:34.208
trying to find someone else
to bring up to her level.

65
00:05:34.209 --> 00:05:35.711
I've made my decision.

66
00:05:37.546 --> 00:05:38.714
Bring her in.

67
00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:40.340
[sighs]

68
00:05:50.100 --> 00:05:51.268
[Ed] Svetlana.

69
00:05:59.443 --> 00:06:00.485
[sighs]

70
00:06:01.236 --> 00:06:02.570
[Danielle] Comrade Zakharova.

71
00:06:02.571 --> 00:06:04.780
I have read the incident report.

72
00:06:04.781 --> 00:06:07.200
and I've come to a decision
about your punishment.

73
00:06:07.201 --> 00:06:08.577
It's irrelevant.

74
00:06:09.369 --> 00:06:10.621
What do you mean?

75
00:06:11.788 --> 00:06:15.959
I've just heard from Star City.
I've been recalled to Moscow.

76
00:06:17.336 --> 00:06:19.463
I am to go home on Unity.

77
00:06:22.883 --> 00:06:25.302
Uh. Unity leaves tomorrow.

78
00:06:27.554 --> 00:06:28.930
Why?

79
00:06:28.931 --> 00:06:34.310
I'm to stand trial for assault and
crimes against a patriot of Soviet Union.

80
00:06:34.311 --> 00:06:36.312
But... Wait. That
doesn't make sense.

81
00:06:36.313 --> 00:06:39.483
The Soviets have never recalled a
cosmonaut for something like this before.

82
00:06:40.275 --> 00:06:43.195
Vasily's family is
connected to the new regime.

83
00:06:52.538 --> 00:06:55.665
{\an8}<i>And with what we've all been
hearing about political retribution</i>

84
00:06:55.666 --> 00:06:57.417
{\an8}<i>under this new
Soviet government.</i>

85
00:06:58.168 --> 00:07:01.838
<i>I just don't feel like I can agree to
send her back under these circumstances.</i>

86
00:07:01.839 --> 00:07:03.506
<i>As the Commander
of Happy Valley.</i>

87
00:07:03.507 --> 00:07:06.718
<i>my first priority is to
the safety of this crew.</i>

88
00:07:07.594 --> 00:07:08.636
[line clicks]

89
00:07:08.637 --> 00:07:11.764
Well. I gotta say I'm with
Commander Poole on this one.

90
00:07:11.765 --> 00:07:14.560
We can't just stand back while
they ship her to some gulag.

91
00:07:15.060 --> 00:07:17.270
I hear you. Will. I do. But...

92
00:07:17.271 --> 00:07:19.730
where this gets tricky
is with the M-7 Charter

93
00:07:19.731 --> 00:07:22.400
that President Wilson
negotiated with Gorbachev.

94
00:07:22.401 --> 00:07:23.776
[Hughes] It says
it pretty clear.

95
00:07:23.777 --> 00:07:27.321
Any nation that desires to recall
one of its citizens from Mars.

96
00:07:27.322 --> 00:07:28.781
it's within their rights.

97
00:07:28.782 --> 00:07:31.534
So we're just gonna kowtow
to this... this lunatic?

98
00:07:31.535 --> 00:07:33.745
No one said anything
about kowtowing.

99
00:07:34.371 --> 00:07:36.540
The president wants to
stand up for what's right.

100
00:07:37.165 --> 00:07:40.294
But history is not made by talking with
only the people that agree with you.

101
00:07:42.546 --> 00:07:44.922
Now tell us more about
this new head of Roscosmos.

102
00:07:44.923 --> 00:07:46.967
So I know who we're
dealing with here.

103
00:07:49.052 --> 00:07:50.636
[liaison] Irina Morozova.

104
00:07:50.637 --> 00:07:52.138
From what little
we know about her.

105
00:07:52.139 --> 00:07:54.891
she's been in the security
and surveillance apparatus

106
00:07:54.892 --> 00:07:57.018
at Star City since '69.

107
00:07:57.019 --> 00:07:59.228
From an elite Russian
family in Moscow.

108
00:07:59.229 --> 00:08:02.481
She seemed to have fallen out of
favor with the Gorbachev regime.

109
00:08:02.482 --> 00:08:06.861
as did much of the KGB. which. we
think. is why she backed Korzhenko.

110
00:08:06.862 --> 00:08:11.157
We've been getting reports that she's
been slowly purging Roscosmos of those

111
00:08:11.158 --> 00:08:12.950
thought to be disloyal
to the new regime.

112
00:08:12.951 --> 00:08:15.995
And it looks like she's settling
scores up on Mars now too.

113
00:08:15.996 --> 00:08:19.665
Cosmonaut Zakharova was an
outspoken supporter of Gorbachev.

114
00:08:19.666 --> 00:08:23.211
Well. I'm sure a
compromise can be found.

115
00:08:23.212 --> 00:08:27.257
If I can hash out a good deal with
the UAW. I guarantee I can with her.

116
00:08:29.218 --> 00:08:30.719
I like working
with the Russians.

117
00:08:32.054 --> 00:08:33.347
They're direct.

118
00:08:34.472 --> 00:08:36.183
{\an8}They don't like beating
around the bush.

119
00:08:37.934 --> 00:08:39.520
We'll just have to talk it out.

120
00:08:44.566 --> 00:08:46.693
Here is the underwear for Libes.

121
00:08:47.694 --> 00:08:50.071
dental floss for Crouse.

122
00:08:50.072 --> 00:08:51.989
socks for Halotek.

123
00:08:51.990 --> 00:08:53.617
- Here we go.
- [Miles] Okay.

124
00:08:54.284 --> 00:08:56.118
I got some more orders.

125
00:08:56.119 --> 00:08:58.204
David Markman wants
more beef jerky.

126
00:08:58.205 --> 00:08:59.205
Mmm.

127
00:08:59.206 --> 00:09:01.583
And Reilly wants more porn.

128
00:09:02.251 --> 00:09:05.086
- [chuckles]
- These are his preferred. uh. genres.

129
00:09:05.087 --> 00:09:08.297
Ah. Reilly. he is a sick fuck.

130
00:09:08.298 --> 00:09:10.091
[chuckles] A sick
fuck with money.

131
00:09:10.092 --> 00:09:12.260
[chuckles] My favorite
kind. [chuckles]

132
00:09:12.261 --> 00:09:14.637
And Lee gave me the next
order for the North Koreans.

133
00:09:14.638 --> 00:09:19.600
They want more fungal cream. more
energy bars. more Fruit of the Loom.

134
00:09:19.601 --> 00:09:21.812
This North Korean
market. Milosh.

135
00:09:22.646 --> 00:09:26.065
This is a gold mine.
[chuckles. speaks Russian]

136
00:09:26.066 --> 00:09:29.318
Speaking of which. uh. any
word on that special request?

137
00:09:29.319 --> 00:09:31.195
Our North Korean
friend was asking.

138
00:09:31.196 --> 00:09:35.075
My associate is working on
it. Tell Lee to be patient.

139
00:09:38.036 --> 00:09:39.036
Your. uh...

140
00:09:39.037 --> 00:09:41.455
Your associate. how long
have you worked with him?

141
00:09:41.456 --> 00:09:43.833
Many years. He is friend.

142
00:09:43.834 --> 00:09:48.171
We worked together on
Moon. Now he is Earthside.

143
00:09:48.172 --> 00:09:51.800
And your associate. would he be
interested in other business ventures?

144
00:09:52.301 --> 00:09:55.386
I mean. like. if we found something
up here that we could sell down there?

145
00:09:55.387 --> 00:10:00.099
[laughs] What could people on
Earth want from this wasteland?

146
00:10:00.100 --> 00:10:03.561
Well. I sent my
daughter a Mars rock.

147
00:10:03.562 --> 00:10:05.313
Well. Sam found it
for me. actually.

148
00:10:05.314 --> 00:10:11.068
but it's like a really
rare volcanic glass.

149
00:10:11.069 --> 00:10:12.154
A rock?

150
00:10:13.488 --> 00:10:14.822
Here. Just listen.

151
00:10:14.823 --> 00:10:19.493
She loved the rock you sent her.
but... [sighs] ...don't get mad.

152
00:10:19.494 --> 00:10:21.370
<i>Um. okay. we were
at the Galleria</i>

153
00:10:21.371 --> 00:10:24.749
<i>and I was just browsing for a new
pair of earrings and. you know...</i>

154
00:10:24.750 --> 00:10:28.127
<i>Of course. Lily was playing with
her favorite new shiny red rock.</i>

155
00:10:28.128 --> 00:10:31.339
<i>And the owner of the jewelry
store started asking me</i>

156
00:10:31.340 --> 00:10:33.592
<i>about where the thing came from.</i>

157
00:10:34.510 --> 00:10:35.927
<i>Well. I told her.</i>

158
00:10:35.928 --> 00:10:40.891
<i>And. get this. she offered me
five grand for it on the spot.</i>

159
00:10:41.391 --> 00:10:44.477
[chuckles] She's... She's
gonna make jewelry out of it.

160
00:10:44.478 --> 00:10:47.147
<i>and she wants more.</i>

161
00:10:48.398 --> 00:10:51.817
I'm thinking if your guy
could get it to Amanda.

162
00:10:51.818 --> 00:10:54.278
this could be a big opportunity.

163
00:10:54.279 --> 00:10:55.364
[Ilya] Mmm.

164
00:10:55.989 --> 00:10:58.908
So now we are
import-export. huh?

165
00:10:58.909 --> 00:11:00.034
Why not?

166
00:11:00.035 --> 00:11:03.080
No. Milosh. this
is not what we do.

167
00:11:04.331 --> 00:11:08.292
I have system. Same
system for years.

168
00:11:08.293 --> 00:11:10.628
Ilya. she made five grand
off a couple ounces.

169
00:11:10.629 --> 00:11:12.672
I'm talking about it's
rare even up here.

170
00:11:12.673 --> 00:11:14.590
Could you imagine what
we could do with that?

171
00:11:14.591 --> 00:11:17.802
No. we have to be
careful. You understand?

172
00:11:17.803 --> 00:11:20.721
Start sending things down.
we'd need more people.

173
00:11:20.722 --> 00:11:23.057
More people means more risk.

174
00:11:23.058 --> 00:11:26.520
More mouths to feed.
More ways to get fucked.

175
00:11:27.062 --> 00:11:30.857
My way is the best way.
Milosh. You understand?

176
00:11:30.858 --> 00:11:31.984
Yeah. I understand.

177
00:11:35.320 --> 00:11:36.988
{\an8}[Hobson] And it
is my sincere hope

178
00:11:36.989 --> 00:11:40.366
that the two of us can find a
reasonable solution to this situation

179
00:11:40.367 --> 00:11:42.703
that is acceptable
to both our nations.

180
00:11:43.370 --> 00:11:44.871
We are partners after all.

181
00:11:44.872 --> 00:11:46.080
[Irina] Indeed. we are.

182
00:11:46.081 --> 00:11:48.666
As partners. we appreciate
your cooperation

183
00:11:48.667 --> 00:11:52.837
in returning Svetlana Zakharova to
the Soviet Union to face justice.

184
00:11:52.838 --> 00:11:56.048
[chuckles] Look. it was just
a little dustup. That's all.

185
00:11:56.049 --> 00:11:57.216
<i>Tempers ran hot.</i>

186
00:11:57.217 --> 00:12:00.928
<i>They're under a lot of pressure to get
the asteroid program up and running.</i>

187
00:12:00.929 --> 00:12:04.390
And from what I'm being
told. Galkin is on the mend.

188
00:12:04.391 --> 00:12:07.560
So this really would be best
handled by Commander Poole in situ.

189
00:12:07.561 --> 00:12:09.730
<i>It is not a question
of his recovery.</i>

190
00:12:10.689 --> 00:12:14.234
Cosmonaut Zakharova broke Soviet
law. Administrator Hobson.

191
00:12:16.195 --> 00:12:19.947
At any rate. the Happy Valley
Commander is on top of the situation.

192
00:12:19.948 --> 00:12:24.160
Our charter clearly states that no
individual member of the M-7 has authority

193
00:12:24.161 --> 00:12:25.913
over base disciplinary action.

194
00:12:26.496 --> 00:12:28.372
That is in the purview
of the base commander.

195
00:12:28.373 --> 00:12:30.667
<i>But this doesn't fall
under base discipline.</i>

196
00:12:31.293 --> 00:12:36.339
As I said. this is about
enforcement of law. Soviet law.

197
00:12:36.340 --> 00:12:41.428
<i>Zakharova's a Soviet citizen and
she assaulted a Soviet citizen.</i>

198
00:12:42.346 --> 00:12:44.680
<i>And the M-7 Charter
also clearly stated</i>

199
00:12:44.681 --> 00:12:48.936
we have the right to recall any
Soviets from Mars at our discretion.

200
00:12:50.187 --> 00:12:52.648
A right we now wish to exercise.

201
00:12:54.608 --> 00:12:57.819
Well. that's the
tricky thing. Irina.

202
00:12:58.820 --> 00:13:03.242
As you know. that agreement was made
when Gorbachev was head of the USSR.

203
00:13:03.825 --> 00:13:09.080
but now with your recent change of
government that you've all experienced...

204
00:13:09.081 --> 00:13:10.581
<i>Am I also to understand that</i>

205
00:13:10.582 --> 00:13:13.459
<i>once Albert Gore became
president of the United States.</i>

206
00:13:13.460 --> 00:13:17.589
all of President Ellen Wilson's
treaties become invalidated?

207
00:13:21.927 --> 00:13:23.220
[Hobson] That...

208
00:13:23.846 --> 00:13:25.138
It is not the same thing.

209
00:13:25.722 --> 00:13:26.723
<i>At all.</i>

210
00:13:27.891 --> 00:13:29.684
Why don't we just cut
to the chase here. okay?

211
00:13:29.685 --> 00:13:31.435
You are insisting
on this because

212
00:13:31.436 --> 00:13:35.356
Vasily Galkin's uncle has
close ties to your new premier.

213
00:13:35.357 --> 00:13:38.609
Propaganda spread by opponents
of the new government.

214
00:13:38.610 --> 00:13:41.112
Galkin's family has
no bearing on this.

215
00:13:41.113 --> 00:13:43.448
As it would have none in
your system of justice.

216
00:13:44.324 --> 00:13:49.829
The simple fact is the United States
is not going to sanction this transfer.

217
00:13:49.830 --> 00:13:51.372
If you don't agree to abide

218
00:13:51.373 --> 00:13:55.127
by the terms we have all
agreed to in the Charter.

219
00:13:55.836 --> 00:13:59.882
<i>then we will be forced to
reconsider participation in the M-7.</i>

220
00:14:01.633 --> 00:14:02.634
[stammers]

221
00:14:08.390 --> 00:14:09.766
[Hobson sighs]

222
00:14:11.185 --> 00:14:13.061
Well. that didn't
go well. did it?

223
00:14:28.243 --> 00:14:30.037
[in Russian] Good day. everyone.

224
00:14:31.163 --> 00:14:33.707
There is much to discuss.

225
00:14:35.167 --> 00:14:36.877
Let's begin.

226
00:14:38.504 --> 00:14:40.047
First order of business.

227
00:14:42.633 --> 00:14:44.884
The Americans have
chosen to disregard

228
00:14:44.885 --> 00:14:47.261
the terms of the Mars Treaty

229
00:14:47.262 --> 00:14:51.307
and are refusing to send
Cosmonaut Zakharova back

230
00:14:51.308 --> 00:14:54.644
to face justice for her
aggression against the nephew

231
00:14:54.645 --> 00:14:58.397
of a highly respected
member of the new politburo.

232
00:14:58.398 --> 00:15:02.735
We must resist
this egregious act.

233
00:15:02.736 --> 00:15:04.237
Our response is in progress.

234
00:15:04.238 --> 00:15:07.031
They will face consequences
for this course of action.

235
00:15:07.032 --> 00:15:08.407
[bureaucrat] Director...

236
00:15:08.408 --> 00:15:12.329
it may be wise to
reconsider this position.

237
00:15:12.913 --> 00:15:15.873
If we hope to reactivate
the asteroid program

238
00:15:15.874 --> 00:15:17.960
Zakharova should
remain at her post.

239
00:15:19.336 --> 00:15:21.337
Are you suggesting
that Zakharova

240
00:15:21.338 --> 00:15:23.881
did not. in fact.
attack Vasily Galkin?

241
00:15:23.882 --> 00:15:25.716
No. I am...

242
00:15:25.717 --> 00:15:29.054
If you were stabbed in
the back. Comrade Babanin.

243
00:15:29.721 --> 00:15:31.974
would you hand the dagger
back to your assailant?

244
00:15:35.102 --> 00:15:37.813
No. of course not.

245
00:15:38.480 --> 00:15:40.523
I did not think so.

246
00:15:40.524 --> 00:15:45.111
We must find out if we can
once again trust the Americans.

247
00:15:45.112 --> 00:15:46.404
To this end.

248
00:15:46.405 --> 00:15:50.199
there will be no reactivation
of the asteroid program

249
00:15:50.200 --> 00:15:54.579
until we know what went wrong
with the Kronos mission.

250
00:15:54.580 --> 00:15:58.041
A tragedy that took the life of
our beloved Comrade Kuznetsov.

251
00:15:58.834 --> 00:16:01.544
Comrade Semenov. you have
the preliminary draft of

252
00:16:01.545 --> 00:16:06.048
the XF Kronos asteroid capture
accident investigation ready for us?

253
00:16:06.049 --> 00:16:07.133
Yes.

254
00:16:07.134 --> 00:16:09.760
Comrade Volkova. would you mind
handing them out for me. please?

255
00:16:09.761 --> 00:16:11.763
[Volkova] Immediately. Comrade.

256
00:16:20.272 --> 00:16:23.358
Please give one to
Margaret Reynolds as well.

257
00:16:24.693 --> 00:16:26.904
I want her to
review the findings.

258
00:16:28.071 --> 00:16:30.531
My apologies. we only
made enough for...

259
00:16:30.532 --> 00:16:32.409
You can give her Babanin's copy.

260
00:16:35.037 --> 00:16:37.331
Comrade Semenov.
please continue.

261
00:16:38.207 --> 00:16:41.000
[Semenov] The American
design was flawed.

262
00:16:41.001 --> 00:16:45.129
The problem was caused by an
underdamped harmonic oscillation.

263
00:16:45.130 --> 00:16:49.675
induced by the spacecraft
altitude control system.

264
00:16:49.676 --> 00:16:53.931
Altitude control thruster
firings on Ranger-1 excited...

265
00:16:55.474 --> 00:16:57.184
[jazz music playing]

266
00:16:59.353 --> 00:17:00.354
[grunts]

267
00:17:40.185 --> 00:17:41.645
[music ends]

268
00:17:46.942 --> 00:17:48.943
[Sam. in English] Commander
Poole's protecting her.

269
00:17:48.944 --> 00:17:51.821
And she's just walking around
up there like nothing happened.

270
00:17:51.822 --> 00:17:53.364
Yukking it up with the XO.

271
00:17:53.365 --> 00:17:55.867
And I heard that Vasily
might be paralyzed too.

272
00:17:55.868 --> 00:17:56.993
Brain-dead.

273
00:17:56.994 --> 00:17:59.329
- That's what Manush told me.
- [Rich] Really?

274
00:17:59.913 --> 00:18:01.789
A cool 20 says Vasily
gets sent home.

275
00:18:01.790 --> 00:18:03.791
and the cosmonaut gets
a slap on the wrist.

276
00:18:03.792 --> 00:18:06.419
No. You really think that?

277
00:18:06.420 --> 00:18:09.839
We gotta spell it out for you? Svetlana.
she's... she's an anointed one.

278
00:18:09.840 --> 00:18:12.925
She's a cosmonaut. And Vasily.
he's just a peasant like us.

279
00:18:12.926 --> 00:18:15.761
I can guarantee you it would
be a very different story

280
00:18:15.762 --> 00:18:18.264
if one of us sends one
of them to the hospital.

281
00:18:18.265 --> 00:18:19.724
- No.
- Very different.

282
00:18:19.725 --> 00:18:22.685
Guys. I mean. Vasily
is kind of an asshole.

283
00:18:22.686 --> 00:18:24.061
[Sam laughs]

284
00:18:24.062 --> 00:18:26.606
What? I mean. you know
it's true. You know it.

285
00:18:26.607 --> 00:18:27.899
And that makes it okay?

286
00:18:27.900 --> 00:18:29.317
What... No. okay.
I'm not saying...

287
00:18:29.318 --> 00:18:33.529
No. the truth is they don't give a
shit if one of us gets hurt or worse.

288
00:18:33.530 --> 00:18:36.408
Hey. Sam. You got a second?

289
00:18:37.117 --> 00:18:38.284
Yeah.

290
00:18:38.285 --> 00:18:40.329
[Maya] It's too much.
It's gotta stop.

291
00:18:41.163 --> 00:18:42.997
[Gerardo] I'm telling
you. that's how it goes.

292
00:18:42.998 --> 00:18:46.251
That obsidian rock. You
remember where you found it?

293
00:18:47.169 --> 00:18:50.130
Yeah. Yeah. It was... It
was by Peckinpah Mesa.

294
00:18:50.714 --> 00:18:51.923
There were a bunch there.

295
00:18:51.924 --> 00:18:54.050
Would you mind taking
me out tomorrow morning?

296
00:18:54.051 --> 00:18:56.845
I think I can sell them back
on Earth. I'll give you a cut.

297
00:18:59.431 --> 00:19:02.016
How can you be thinking about
selling fucking rocks right now

298
00:19:02.017 --> 00:19:04.227
when Vasily's laying in
a hyperbaric chamber?

299
00:19:04.228 --> 00:19:06.270
There's nothing we can
do about that right now.

300
00:19:06.271 --> 00:19:09.440
except not play by those
motherfuckers' rules.

301
00:19:09.441 --> 00:19:12.735
So this is about justice. not
about filling your pockets?

302
00:19:12.736 --> 00:19:14.862
Why can't it be about both?

303
00:19:14.863 --> 00:19:17.156
Come on. I cut a deal
with the suit soop

304
00:19:17.157 --> 00:19:19.659
and he's gonna let me skip the
line and get a pressure suit.

305
00:19:19.660 --> 00:19:21.578
I don't have rover
access and you do.

306
00:19:24.498 --> 00:19:25.541
So you in?

307
00:19:28.001 --> 00:19:29.044
No.

308
00:19:29.878 --> 00:19:31.129
Fine. I'll hoof it.

309
00:19:35.217 --> 00:19:36.301
[Sam scoffs]

310
00:19:53.026 --> 00:19:54.236
[sighs]

311
00:20:01.493 --> 00:20:02.494
[sighs]

312
00:20:45.037 --> 00:20:46.038
Damn it.

313
00:20:49.291 --> 00:20:50.292
[Volkova] Wait.

314
00:20:55.339 --> 00:20:56.340
May I?

315
00:20:58.842 --> 00:21:00.552
[footsteps departing]

316
00:21:26.745 --> 00:21:28.330
Same diameter and weight.

317
00:21:32.209 --> 00:21:33.210
Clever.

318
00:21:33.794 --> 00:21:35.963
If only the coffee
were worth the effort.

319
00:21:36.505 --> 00:21:38.549
I'll take anything
right about now.

320
00:21:39.174 --> 00:21:40.217
[Volkova] Hmm.

321
00:21:41.343 --> 00:21:42.344
[Margo] Thank you.

322
00:21:44.596 --> 00:21:47.182
[coins clatter]

323
00:21:50.227 --> 00:21:52.563
[machine whirs]

324
00:21:53.438 --> 00:21:55.232
[machine clicking]

325
00:22:17.045 --> 00:22:21.383
Are these spin vector calculations for
the new asteroid capture protocols?

326
00:22:23.343 --> 00:22:24.595
Yes.

327
00:22:25.596 --> 00:22:26.596
Yes. and I admit

328
00:22:26.597 --> 00:22:30.434
I'm unable to get the finite element
model to replicate consistently.

329
00:22:31.852 --> 00:22:32.936
May I?

330
00:22:50.204 --> 00:22:52.121
If you switch reference frames.

331
00:22:52.122 --> 00:22:55.375
you might have better luck
with inverting the matrices.

332
00:22:58.921 --> 00:22:59.922
Thank you.

333
00:23:00.672 --> 00:23:01.673
We're even.

334
00:23:05.052 --> 00:23:07.846
Uh. Tatyana
Alexandrovna Volkova.

335
00:23:11.433 --> 00:23:13.351
I'm Margaret.

336
00:23:13.352 --> 00:23:16.396
I know. We all know who you are.

337
00:23:18.774 --> 00:23:21.234
No one even so much
as says. "Hello."

338
00:23:21.235 --> 00:23:22.736
Director Morozova...

339
00:23:25.572 --> 00:23:29.243
Well. she made it very clear that.
uh. we should keep our distance.

340
00:23:30.369 --> 00:23:31.411
Oh.

341
00:23:33.247 --> 00:23:35.082
So why did you help me just now?

342
00:23:36.708 --> 00:23:39.086
Well. a woman without
coffee is a dangerous woman.

343
00:23:39.795 --> 00:23:41.296
[Margo chuckles]

344
00:23:43.507 --> 00:23:44.925
Very true.

345
00:23:49.179 --> 00:23:50.889
[Margo chuckles]

346
00:24:00.524 --> 00:24:01.525
[Margo] Good night.

347
00:24:03.193 --> 00:24:04.778
Good night. Ms. Reynolds.

348
00:24:12.452 --> 00:24:14.495
Have you tried rebooting
the primary root server?

349
00:24:14.496 --> 00:24:17.374
Twice. Also tried cycling
the CPU processors.

350
00:24:17.916 --> 00:24:19.751
Zilch. It's still
all in Cyrillic.

351
00:24:24.089 --> 00:24:25.090
Be right back.

352
00:24:29.011 --> 00:24:32.513
Yevgeniy. you know what's going
on with the user interface?

353
00:24:32.514 --> 00:24:33.931
It's all in Cyrillic.

354
00:24:33.932 --> 00:24:37.393
Yes. Roscosmos decided to
revert Ops computer system

355
00:24:37.394 --> 00:24:39.979
back to original
Soviet parameters.

356
00:24:39.980 --> 00:24:43.317
What? That is going to
severely disrupt operations.

357
00:24:43.942 --> 00:24:46.402
As the commander of this base.
any changes need to be run...

358
00:24:46.403 --> 00:24:49.156
Soviet Union no longer recognizes
your role as commander.

359
00:24:50.324 --> 00:24:51.950
You can't be serious.

360
00:24:52.951 --> 00:24:53.952
I'm sorry.

361
00:24:57.956 --> 00:24:59.832
Son of a bitch.

362
00:24:59.833 --> 00:25:03.044
I mean. I thought we were
beyond all this bullshit.

363
00:25:03.045 --> 00:25:06.589
It looks like all the other Soviet-aligned
countries are backing their play.

364
00:25:06.590 --> 00:25:10.511
ESA. JAXA are still with us.
ISRO's playing it coy as usual.

365
00:25:12.846 --> 00:25:14.889
What's Houston got to
say about all this?

366
00:25:14.890 --> 00:25:18.935
Well. Hobson's getting into it with
Moscow. but it's not looking good.

367
00:25:18.936 --> 00:25:22.981
They're digging in their heels. They
still want Svetlana sent back to Earth.

368
00:25:24.775 --> 00:25:27.777
Wish Kuz was here. He wouldn't
have put up with any of this shit.

369
00:25:27.778 --> 00:25:29.530
Yeah. you got that right.

370
00:25:30.280 --> 00:25:33.658
I doubt this is over. so I want
you all to do safety checks.

371
00:25:33.659 --> 00:25:37.828
Then run full diagnostics on all
your equipment. your stations.

372
00:25:37.829 --> 00:25:39.789
make sure everything's
still in working order.

373
00:25:39.790 --> 00:25:43.084
Palmer. let's do a security
sweep of the entire base.

374
00:25:43.085 --> 00:25:44.919
Make sure they're not
up to something else.

375
00:25:44.920 --> 00:25:48.589
And I want to put someone outside of
Svetlana Zakharova's quarters immediately

376
00:25:48.590 --> 00:25:50.676
to make sure the Soviets
don't try and grab her.

377
00:25:51.260 --> 00:25:52.468
Good idea.

378
00:25:52.469 --> 00:25:54.637
All right. you've all
got your marching orders.

379
00:25:54.638 --> 00:25:56.681
Let's meet back
here in two hours.

380
00:25:56.682 --> 00:25:58.058
[Ed. Danielle] All right.

381
00:26:07.025 --> 00:26:09.235
[Gore. on phone] How is
this even possible. Eli?

382
00:26:09.236 --> 00:26:10.153
Well. sir. I...

383
00:26:10.154 --> 00:26:13.614
<i>A month ago. Happy Valley was a
beacon of international cooperation.</i>

384
00:26:13.615 --> 00:26:16.200
<i>And now it's the front
line of a new Cold War.</i>

385
00:26:16.201 --> 00:26:20.830
Mr. President. Al. I'm working on it.
but this new director of Roscosmos...

386
00:26:20.831 --> 00:26:23.165
<i>You remember my speech
in Chicago. don't you?</i>

387
00:26:23.166 --> 00:26:25.459
<i>I said the Cold War was over.</i>

388
00:26:25.460 --> 00:26:28.337
<i>You think they're not going to play
that on repeat until election day?</i>

389
00:26:28.338 --> 00:26:31.300
That is not gonna happen. sir.
I am going to resolve this.

390
00:26:31.925 --> 00:26:33.050
<i>See that you do.</i>

391
00:26:33.051 --> 00:26:35.137
- And may I...
- [line clicks. beeps]

392
00:26:37.472 --> 00:26:38.557
[phone beeps]

393
00:26:40.851 --> 00:26:41.851
[sighs]

394
00:26:41.852 --> 00:26:45.188
[Christine Francis] The future of the M-7
alliance is being called into question

395
00:26:45.189 --> 00:26:47.148
{\an8}<i>in the wake of a
diplomatic crisis</i>

396
00:26:47.149 --> 00:26:51.068
{\an8}<i>over the legal status of
Cosmonaut Svetlana Zakharova.</i>

397
00:26:51.069 --> 00:26:55.740
{\an8}<i>International cooperation has been a
hallmark of the Mars colony to this point.</i>

398
00:26:55.741 --> 00:26:57.491
{\an8}<i>But that seems to
have evaporated</i>

399
00:26:57.492 --> 00:27:02.747
{\an8}<i>as several M-7 nations are refusing to
back the Gore administration's efforts</i>

400
00:27:02.748 --> 00:27:06.876
{\an8}<i>to protect Zakharova from
reprisals by the new Soviet regime.</i>

401
00:27:06.877 --> 00:27:08.878
{\an8}<i>The growing conflict
has fueled concerns</i>

402
00:27:08.879 --> 00:27:12.381
{\an8}<i>that this may reignite tensions
between the two superpowers</i>

403
00:27:12.382 --> 00:27:15.635
{\an8}<i>for the first time
since the early 1990s.</i>

404
00:27:15.636 --> 00:27:17.721
{\an8}<i>Because of what is at stake.</i>

405
00:27:18.472 --> 00:27:21.308
{\an8}<i>this matter must be
resolved expeditiously.</i>

406
00:27:22.226 --> 00:27:25.020
{\an8}<i>but deliberately and without
any rush to judgment.</i>

407
00:27:25.771 --> 00:27:28.648
{\an8}<i>This is the question
that's on everybody's mind.</i>

408
00:27:28.649 --> 00:27:31.275
{\an8}<i>Are you worried about how
the current diplomatic crisis</i>

409
00:27:31.276 --> 00:27:33.986
{\an8}<i>between the United States
and the Soviet Union</i>

410
00:27:33.987 --> 00:27:36.698
<i>will impact Helios's
financial position?</i>

411
00:27:37.407 --> 00:27:41.118
<i>Not at all. Helios is a
multinational corporation.</i>

412
00:27:41.119 --> 00:27:43.413
- We don't have a dog in this fight.
- [Miles] Shaw.

413
00:27:43.997 --> 00:27:45.749
You got my suit
and camera ready?

414
00:27:46.625 --> 00:27:47.835
[Shaw] Pretty cool. huh?

415
00:27:48.585 --> 00:27:50.795
Dev Ayesa back in charge.

416
00:27:50.796 --> 00:27:52.880
Can't wait till he kicks
some ass down there.

417
00:27:52.881 --> 00:27:54.173
Yeah. fuck that guy.

418
00:27:54.174 --> 00:27:55.800
What's your beef with Dev?

419
00:27:55.801 --> 00:27:58.011
Man. he put a lot of
people I know out of work.

420
00:27:58.512 --> 00:28:00.472
Mr. Buzzkill over here.

421
00:28:01.932 --> 00:28:04.350
Here's your camera
and cooling garment.

422
00:28:04.351 --> 00:28:05.811
I'll bring your suit out to you.

423
00:28:07.646 --> 00:28:09.731
Store your shit in one of
those lockers over there.

424
00:28:12.359 --> 00:28:15.695
<i>'cause Helios is a service company.
I'm here to change all that.</i>

425
00:28:15.696 --> 00:28:17.864
<i>To get back to the
original vision.</i>

426
00:28:17.865 --> 00:28:20.032
{\an8}<i>Building a thriving
colony on Mars.</i>

427
00:28:20.033 --> 00:28:21.869
{\an8}<i>Not just for astronauts
and scientists.</i>

428
00:28:22.744 --> 00:28:25.289
{\an8}<i>but for anyone who wants
to make the journey.</i>

429
00:28:30.127 --> 00:28:31.461
[Miles] Hey. how you doing?

430
00:28:32.629 --> 00:28:34.339
My first time out
on the surface.

431
00:28:35.674 --> 00:28:38.635
I'm gonna take some
pictures for the kiddos.

432
00:28:47.853 --> 00:28:50.105
[sighs] And here's your suit.

433
00:28:59.072 --> 00:29:00.616
Can I get one of those suits?

434
00:29:01.617 --> 00:29:02.868
They're all booked.

435
00:29:03.952 --> 00:29:07.372
If you want to get out there today.
this is the only one I got available.

436
00:29:10.209 --> 00:29:11.793
- [helmet clicks]
- [grunts]

437
00:29:14.046 --> 00:29:15.379
[no audible dialogue]

438
00:29:15.380 --> 00:29:17.007
[Shaw] You gotta key your radio.

439
00:29:18.425 --> 00:29:20.135
Is it supposed to
smell like this?

440
00:29:34.816 --> 00:29:36.610
[Miles] They're on
that mesa. pilgrim.

441
00:29:38.237 --> 00:29:40.405
They've been following
us for two days.

442
00:29:41.240 --> 00:29:43.992
Only one tribe wears a
war bonnet like that.

443
00:29:44.576 --> 00:29:46.577
Noyuhka Comanche.

444
00:29:46.578 --> 00:29:47.913
Don't look. you fool!

445
00:29:53.418 --> 00:29:55.254
[breathes heavily]

446
00:29:57.172 --> 00:30:00.259
[grunting] Where the
hell are these things?

447
00:30:01.301 --> 00:30:03.011
This is where Sam
said they'd be.

448
00:30:12.020 --> 00:30:13.647
[breathes heavily]

449
00:30:26.577 --> 00:30:29.246
[breathes heavily] Bingo.

450
00:30:59.860 --> 00:31:02.738
[heavy breathing continues]

451
00:31:38.524 --> 00:31:39.982
[grunts]

452
00:31:39.983 --> 00:31:42.693
[panting] Goddamn it!

453
00:31:42.694 --> 00:31:43.778
[grunts] Fuck!

454
00:31:43.779 --> 00:31:46.614
[panting]

455
00:31:46.615 --> 00:31:48.950
Oh. man! [grunts. shouts]

456
00:31:48.951 --> 00:31:50.869
[screaming]

457
00:32:01.088 --> 00:32:02.214
Commander Poole?

458
00:32:03.090 --> 00:32:04.925
Uh. sorry to bother you...

459
00:32:05.551 --> 00:32:06.926
What's on your mind?

460
00:32:06.927 --> 00:32:08.220
Well. uh...

461
00:32:10.097 --> 00:32:11.640
Ma'am. downstairs. we're. um.

462
00:32:12.891 --> 00:32:16.478
concerned about the way you dealt
with-with Svetlana Zakharova.

463
00:32:18.146 --> 00:32:19.188
Who's we?

464
00:32:19.189 --> 00:32:20.899
Some of us Helios workers.

465
00:32:21.942 --> 00:32:23.901
Look. Vasily was our colleague

466
00:32:23.902 --> 00:32:26.404
and we feel like the punishment
cosmonaut Zakharova receives

467
00:32:26.405 --> 00:32:27.697
should be more appropriate.

468
00:32:27.698 --> 00:32:31.159
How do you know what her
punishment's gonna be?

469
00:32:31.743 --> 00:32:34.412
Well. we heard that you might
not be sending her back.

470
00:32:34.413 --> 00:32:35.539
You heard?

471
00:32:36.456 --> 00:32:37.582
I see.

472
00:32:37.583 --> 00:32:38.667
Right.

473
00:32:39.585 --> 00:32:42.378
Well. I talked to
everybody who was there.

474
00:32:42.379 --> 00:32:45.716
and you have no idea how
complicated the situation is.

475
00:32:47.759 --> 00:32:50.720
- Now. if you'll. excuse me...
- She put him in a hyperbaric chamber.

476
00:32:50.721 --> 00:32:54.140
I mean. the nitrogen in his blood could
lead to a stroke. paralysis or worse.

477
00:32:54.141 --> 00:32:56.560
And she's just walking around
as if it's another day?

478
00:32:57.895 --> 00:32:59.062
It's not right.

479
00:33:00.147 --> 00:33:01.565
You know it's not right.

480
00:33:09.406 --> 00:33:10.616
[sighs]

481
00:33:16.038 --> 00:33:18.415
[beeping]

482
00:33:25.672 --> 00:33:26.882
[Danielle sighs]

483
00:33:28.175 --> 00:33:29.510
How's he progressing. doc?

484
00:33:30.636 --> 00:33:34.097
Arterial gas embolism
is the main concern.

485
00:33:35.265 --> 00:33:36.517
No way to predict.

486
00:33:37.809 --> 00:33:40.479
But he is strong. We can hope.

487
00:33:41.438 --> 00:33:43.190
What do you think
of all this mess?

488
00:33:45.025 --> 00:33:48.403
You and I. we've
been through worse.

489
00:34:04.461 --> 00:34:06.254
Hey. where's Miles?

490
00:34:06.255 --> 00:34:08.714
We gotta get the obsidian into
the hopper cargo before launch.

491
00:34:08.715 --> 00:34:10.091
How should I know. Rich?

492
00:34:10.092 --> 00:34:11.510
Thought you went with him.

493
00:34:12.010 --> 00:34:13.762
No. no. he...

494
00:34:14.888 --> 00:34:16.723
He asked me. but I said no.

495
00:34:18.183 --> 00:34:19.768
He should have been back by now.

496
00:34:22.020 --> 00:34:23.772
It's been almost five hours.

497
00:34:27.192 --> 00:34:28.360
We need to go find him.

498
00:34:31.154 --> 00:34:32.906
[Sam] Miles. Sam. Do you read?

499
00:34:34.658 --> 00:34:36.952
Miles. Samantha.
do you read? Over.

500
00:34:42.123 --> 00:34:45.834
Waters. rover 7. I'm arriving
at Peckinpah Mesa now.

501
00:34:45.835 --> 00:34:48.588
- I think I see where he was headed.
- [Rich] Copy that.

502
00:34:48.589 --> 00:34:52.467
[Sam breathing heavily]

503
00:35:16.491 --> 00:35:20.454
[whispering] No. no. no. No. no.

504
00:35:30.506 --> 00:35:33.132
Thank God. Miles?
Miles. are you okay?

505
00:35:33.133 --> 00:35:35.677
Miles. Miles. Miles!

506
00:35:37.679 --> 00:35:40.307
[suit beeping]

507
00:35:43.894 --> 00:35:47.272
[beeping continues]

508
00:36:01.870 --> 00:36:05.706
Sam. you found me. You found me.

509
00:36:05.707 --> 00:36:09.545
Thank God. Thank God. You
gotta get me out of here. Sam.

510
00:36:13.090 --> 00:36:14.091
What happened?

511
00:36:16.385 --> 00:36:17.844
[sighs]

512
00:36:17.845 --> 00:36:21.931
Can you hear me? How the
hell did you get down there?

513
00:36:21.932 --> 00:36:24.684
[no audible dialogue]

514
00:36:24.685 --> 00:36:27.979
Radio must be busted. Hang on.
I'm gonna get you out of there.

515
00:36:27.980 --> 00:36:29.064
[sniffs]

516
00:36:29.606 --> 00:36:32.609
[machine whirring]

517
00:36:39.241 --> 00:36:41.076
[machine powers down]

518
00:36:43.871 --> 00:36:45.873
[machine whirring]

519
00:36:54.756 --> 00:36:56.007
[Sam sighs]

520
00:36:56.008 --> 00:36:58.760
[grunts. pants]

521
00:37:00.262 --> 00:37:02.890
[breathing heavily]

522
00:37:04.850 --> 00:37:06.559
[pants. grunts]

523
00:37:06.560 --> 00:37:11.355
I fell and I think I
gashed my arm when I fell.

524
00:37:11.356 --> 00:37:12.940
Thank you for coming to get me.

525
00:37:12.941 --> 00:37:14.442
You fucking asshole!

526
00:37:14.443 --> 00:37:16.444
- What the fuck is wrong with you?
- Sam!

527
00:37:16.445 --> 00:37:19.238
That tank in the Helios suit is
the only reason you're not dead!

528
00:37:19.239 --> 00:37:21.532
- Sam. relax!
- What the fuck is wrong with you?

529
00:37:21.533 --> 00:37:23.326
Sam. Sam. calm down.

530
00:37:23.327 --> 00:37:26.038
[panting]

531
00:37:26.830 --> 00:37:28.832
[panting]

532
00:37:33.629 --> 00:37:34.630
Hold still.

533
00:37:38.592 --> 00:37:39.676
Ow.

534
00:37:40.719 --> 00:37:41.970
Take it easy.

535
00:37:53.065 --> 00:37:54.441
Okay. all done.

536
00:37:56.109 --> 00:37:57.110
Thanks.

537
00:38:08.413 --> 00:38:12.709
[Rich. on radio] Rover 7. Waters. come
in. Have you located Miles? Come in.

538
00:38:13.377 --> 00:38:15.546
- We. uh... We should get back.
- Yeah.

539
00:38:21.134 --> 00:38:25.389
Waters. rover 7. I found him. All
is fine. We're heading back soon.

540
00:38:26.181 --> 00:38:29.518
[Rich] Great news. rover 7. Please
smack him in the head for me.

541
00:38:48.453 --> 00:38:49.955
Is this accurate?

542
00:38:52.583 --> 00:38:53.750
Yes.

543
00:38:58.005 --> 00:38:59.256
[beeping]

544
00:39:01.425 --> 00:39:02.592
[Semenov on phone. indistinct]

545
00:39:02.593 --> 00:39:04.051
[in Russian] Come
in to my office.

546
00:39:04.052 --> 00:39:05.220
[Semenov speaks Russian]

547
00:39:08.849 --> 00:39:09.892
[in English] Sit.

548
00:39:11.435 --> 00:39:12.686
I want you here.

549
00:39:23.071 --> 00:39:25.072
[in Russian] Have a
seat. Comrade Semenov.

550
00:39:25.073 --> 00:39:28.492
We were just going over
the accident report

551
00:39:28.493 --> 00:39:32.414
issued by your department.

552
00:39:33.123 --> 00:39:34.958
Is there some problem?

553
00:39:36.001 --> 00:39:37.586
[in English] Tell
him what you told me.

554
00:39:39.796 --> 00:39:44.175
There was a manufacturing error
in the asteroid anchor bolts

555
00:39:44.176 --> 00:39:49.181
that were designed and built by Roscosmos.
but it wasn't caught by quality control.

556
00:39:50.307 --> 00:39:52.099
They did not meet specifications

557
00:39:52.100 --> 00:39:54.727
and should not have been
certified for flight.

558
00:39:54.728 --> 00:39:57.981
That was one of the main
underlying causes of the failure.

559
00:39:59.316 --> 00:40:02.945
What about Commander Baldwin
sanctioning an emergency EVA?

560
00:40:05.155 --> 00:40:08.783
Your report was quite clear about
the command and control issues.

561
00:40:08.784 --> 00:40:12.203
but even if everything had
gone according to plan.

562
00:40:12.204 --> 00:40:14.248
those anchor bolts
would have failed.

563
00:40:14.998 --> 00:40:16.500
And so would the mission.

564
00:40:18.085 --> 00:40:19.795
Your report doesn't
mention this.

565
00:40:21.088 --> 00:40:22.380
[speaks Russian]

566
00:40:22.381 --> 00:40:23.881
[in English] I will not sit here

567
00:40:23.882 --> 00:40:26.133
and listen to an American
making unfounded accusation...

568
00:40:26.134 --> 00:40:30.514
You will sit here until
you are dismissed.

569
00:40:36.353 --> 00:40:41.566
[clears throat] When they get this.
NASA will double-check every calculation

570
00:40:41.567 --> 00:40:44.611
before combining it in
the joint incident report.

571
00:40:45.320 --> 00:40:50.200
They'll realize that the extrapolated
tensile yield strengths of the bolts

572
00:40:51.451 --> 00:40:53.369
couldn't possibly be correct.

573
00:40:53.370 --> 00:40:56.498
And Roscosmos would be
accused then of a cover-up.

574
00:40:57.666 --> 00:41:02.796
And President Korzhenko's government
embarrassed before the entire world.

575
00:41:03.714 --> 00:41:04.797
[in Russian] Director. I...

576
00:41:04.798 --> 00:41:06.758
[Irina] You're a good engineer.

577
00:41:07.384 --> 00:41:09.303
You knew about this. didn't you?

578
00:41:10.721 --> 00:41:12.722
But you didn't include
it in the report.

579
00:41:12.723 --> 00:41:13.849
Why?

580
00:41:18.854 --> 00:41:24.109
It was a units error made
early in fabrication.

581
00:41:24.693 --> 00:41:28.738
NASA sent the torque
test specifications

582
00:41:28.739 --> 00:41:32.743
in pound-feet. but we
work in Newton-meters.

583
00:41:34.578 --> 00:41:38.123
And someone screwed
up the conversion.

584
00:41:39.416 --> 00:41:43.336
The bolts passed
and we flew them.

585
00:41:43.337 --> 00:41:46.423
Only after the
accident did we...

586
00:41:47.508 --> 00:41:48.675
[sighs]

587
00:41:49.718 --> 00:41:51.052
discover the error.

588
00:41:51.053 --> 00:41:53.180
Who screwed up the conversion?

589
00:41:56.391 --> 00:41:58.809
My team performed
the calculations

590
00:41:58.810 --> 00:42:00.896
and therefore I am responsible.

591
00:42:03.440 --> 00:42:04.858
Finally...

592
00:42:05.484 --> 00:42:08.695
some accountability.

593
00:42:11.490 --> 00:42:14.159
[in English] Excellent
work. Margaret. Stay here.

594
00:42:17.329 --> 00:42:19.623
[in Russian] Come. Kirill.

595
00:42:26.046 --> 00:42:27.214
[door opens]

596
00:42:50.195 --> 00:42:53.323
[footsteps approaching]

597
00:43:02.583 --> 00:43:07.254
[in English] It's a poem
Pushkin wrote in 1825.

598
00:43:08.630 --> 00:43:14.052
He wrote it to Anna Petrovna
Kern. with whom he had an affair.

599
00:43:17.556 --> 00:43:23.562
[in Russian] "Remote in my darkened
exile. the days dragged by so slowly.

600
00:43:24.646 --> 00:43:27.274
Without grace.
Without inspiration.

601
00:43:28.025 --> 00:43:31.695
Without tears. Without
life. Without love.

602
00:43:33.113 --> 00:43:36.950
Then my spirit woke and
you... you appeared again.

603
00:43:38.202 --> 00:43:44.082
Like a transient vision.
Like pure beauty's spirit."

604
00:43:50.088 --> 00:43:52.925
[in English] You did a service
today to the Soviet Union.

605
00:43:54.384 --> 00:43:55.469
And to me.

606
00:44:03.477 --> 00:44:04.770
I want you to have this.

607
00:44:06.647 --> 00:44:11.235
It's a picture of the engineers
of our ground control in 1969.

608
00:44:13.820 --> 00:44:14.820
Sergei?

609
00:44:14.821 --> 00:44:15.906
You knew him?

610
00:44:16.490 --> 00:44:17.698
Yes.

611
00:44:17.699 --> 00:44:20.202
We worked together. A long time.

612
00:44:20.911 --> 00:44:22.871
He was a close friend.

613
00:44:24.665 --> 00:44:28.836
Please accept this as a token of my
appreciation of what you've done today.

614
00:44:32.422 --> 00:44:33.757
What will happen to him?

615
00:44:35.384 --> 00:44:36.385
To Kirill?

616
00:44:37.177 --> 00:44:39.054
He will find a new employment.

617
00:44:44.810 --> 00:44:50.399
I wanted you here because I
know what you're capable of.

618
00:44:51.149 --> 00:44:54.318
All of them. they're afraid.

619
00:44:54.319 --> 00:44:56.904
Afraid of their own shadows.

620
00:44:56.905 --> 00:44:58.407
You are different.

621
00:44:59.658 --> 00:45:02.077
The Americans took
you for granted.

622
00:45:02.870 --> 00:45:03.954
I will not.

623
00:45:05.914 --> 00:45:09.251
And I assure you the
work we will do together

624
00:45:10.794 --> 00:45:13.213
will take us far
into the cosmos.

625
00:45:15.549 --> 00:45:17.301
Thank you. Director.

626
00:45:31.773 --> 00:45:33.774
[electronic voice]
Pick up the pace.

627
00:45:33.775 --> 00:45:35.693
- Pick up the pace.
- [panting]

628
00:45:35.694 --> 00:45:38.863
<i>Pick up the pace.
Pick up the pace.</i>

629
00:45:38.864 --> 00:45:41.033
- Shut up.
- Pick up the pace.

630
00:45:41.700 --> 00:45:45.245
- Pick up the pace. Pick up the pace.
- Shut the fuck up!

631
00:45:45.746 --> 00:45:46.872
<i>Pick up the pace.</i>

632
00:45:47.623 --> 00:45:50.333
- Pick up the pace.
- Shut the fuck up!

633
00:45:50.334 --> 00:45:52.627
- You fucking piece of shit!
- Pick up the pace.

634
00:45:52.628 --> 00:45:54.838
Eli. what's going on?

635
00:45:55.714 --> 00:45:57.674
I'm sorry. I just...

636
00:46:01.053 --> 00:46:02.553
It wouldn't shut the fuck up.

637
00:46:02.554 --> 00:46:04.723
We both know the bike
isn't the problem.

638
00:46:05.933 --> 00:46:07.142
I know. I'm sorry.

639
00:46:08.060 --> 00:46:11.730
The president tore into
me. He was pretty peeved.

640
00:46:13.482 --> 00:46:14.483
How peeved?

641
00:46:15.025 --> 00:46:19.988
Well. he may have implied that I have
single-handedly brought back the Cold War.

642
00:46:20.822 --> 00:46:21.907
[groans]

643
00:46:22.741 --> 00:46:25.660
I'm sorry. I know
how hard this job is.

644
00:46:25.661 --> 00:46:28.788
- I'm fine. It's just...
- You're not fine. Eli.

645
00:46:28.789 --> 00:46:31.541
Your cholesterol's up
again. You're not sleeping.

646
00:46:31.542 --> 00:46:34.168
You can barely sit down with
your hemorrhoids flaring up.

647
00:46:34.169 --> 00:46:36.838
Is this you trying to
make me feel better. Kath?

648
00:46:36.839 --> 00:46:39.466
You didn't have
to take this job.

649
00:46:41.051 --> 00:46:42.052
I know.

650
00:46:43.887 --> 00:46:46.013
I just... I felt it was...

651
00:46:46.014 --> 00:46:47.431
- Your duty.
- Yeah.

652
00:46:47.432 --> 00:46:50.227
I know. But there's
no end to that.

653
00:46:50.894 --> 00:46:54.690
It's not like one day you wake up and
decide you've made enough of a difference.

654
00:46:55.190 --> 00:46:59.111
The only difference I'm making now
is destroying our alliance on Mars.

655
00:47:00.571 --> 00:47:04.074
Well. you'll figure it
out. hon. You always do.

656
00:47:04.867 --> 00:47:06.910
[sighs. chuckles]

657
00:47:11.665 --> 00:47:14.126
- I don't deserve you.
- Hmm. No. you don't.

658
00:47:15.794 --> 00:47:19.005
It's only a few more years. I
promise I will make it up to you.

659
00:47:19.006 --> 00:47:21.966
We're supposed to be enjoying
our retirement by now.

660
00:47:21.967 --> 00:47:23.467
traveling around the world.

661
00:47:23.468 --> 00:47:25.469
We have our whole
lives to travel.

662
00:47:25.470 --> 00:47:29.348
We may not have knees to walk on by the
time you're done making a difference.

663
00:47:29.349 --> 00:47:33.811
[chuckles] Well. a beach in Aruba does
sound really good right about now.

664
00:47:33.812 --> 00:47:36.606
Mmm. Or a cruise down the Nile.

665
00:47:36.607 --> 00:47:38.900
- [chuckles]
- Oh. you know what?

666
00:47:38.901 --> 00:47:41.737
I read about this
temple in India.

667
00:47:43.238 --> 00:47:44.239
India?

668
00:47:44.740 --> 00:47:46.866
It was beautiful. Eli.

669
00:47:46.867 --> 00:47:48.868
It's not the Taj Mahal.

670
00:47:48.869 --> 00:47:50.786
It's in the south.

671
00:47:50.787 --> 00:47:53.665
What is that city called
near the Indian Ocean?

672
00:47:57.503 --> 00:47:58.504
Eli?

673
00:48:01.131 --> 00:48:02.966
[mutters] No. I...
I just... I...

674
00:48:07.095 --> 00:48:10.515
I think I just
figured something out.

675
00:48:10.516 --> 00:48:13.184
- I got to go back to CSC.
- Now?

676
00:48:13.185 --> 00:48:14.810
Thank you. I love you.

677
00:48:14.811 --> 00:48:16.271
Eli.

678
00:48:17.731 --> 00:48:19.483
You're still in your sweatpants.

679
00:48:25.697 --> 00:48:26.823
India?

680
00:48:27.324 --> 00:48:29.493
They're the only neutral
country in the M-7.

681
00:48:30.285 --> 00:48:32.788
They've agreed to accept Svetlana
when she gets back to Earth.

682
00:48:33.372 --> 00:48:35.581
She's gonna be put
on trial in India?

683
00:48:35.582 --> 00:48:38.876
Korzhenko and President Gore
have already approved it.

684
00:48:38.877 --> 00:48:40.419
And once she's on Unity.

685
00:48:40.420 --> 00:48:43.841
Roscosmos has agreed to abide by
the terms of the Mars Charter.

686
00:48:44.508 --> 00:48:46.384
and I'd be back in full
command of the base.

687
00:48:46.385 --> 00:48:48.970
Ah. that's all well and good.
But what about Svetlana?

688
00:48:48.971 --> 00:48:50.721
We can't just throw
her to the wolves.

689
00:48:50.722 --> 00:48:52.056
No. of course not.

690
00:48:52.057 --> 00:48:53.724
It'll be a fair trial.

691
00:48:53.725 --> 00:48:56.269
With an independent judge
looking at all the evidence.

692
00:48:56.270 --> 00:48:58.521
You really think the Soviets
are gonna abide by this deal?

693
00:48:58.522 --> 00:49:00.565
The State Department's
already signed off on it.

694
00:49:00.566 --> 00:49:03.985
They feel that with
the security protocols.

695
00:49:03.986 --> 00:49:06.404
we can prevent any
kind of retribution.

696
00:49:06.405 --> 00:49:09.323
Bunch of pencil dicks trying
to cover their own ass.

697
00:49:09.324 --> 00:49:13.245
[stammers] This isn't right.
You... You need to refuse.

698
00:49:14.079 --> 00:49:15.746
Yeah. just tell
him to go to hell.

699
00:49:15.747 --> 00:49:18.584
Ed. I've already agreed.

700
00:49:19.293 --> 00:49:20.294
You what?

701
00:49:20.794 --> 00:49:24.839
Svetlana. she's not blameless
in all of this. all right?

702
00:49:24.840 --> 00:49:27.967
She seriously injured
a Helios worker.

703
00:49:27.968 --> 00:49:31.846
Intentional or not. there's got to be
some real repercussions for what she did.

704
00:49:31.847 --> 00:49:36.350
You need to back me on this. Dani.
Svetlana is one of our best. right?

705
00:49:36.351 --> 00:49:41.356
[stammers] And she-she's...
she's important to this base.

706
00:49:42.357 --> 00:49:45.152
And-And she's important to
the asteroid capture team.

707
00:49:46.028 --> 00:49:47.236
- I know that.
- Uh-uh.

708
00:49:47.237 --> 00:49:50.949
Don't send her back. No. you...
No. you... you find another way.

709
00:49:51.950 --> 00:49:52.951
I can't.

710
00:49:54.244 --> 00:49:55.245
You won't.

711
00:49:57.748 --> 00:49:58.999
I can't and I won't.

712
00:50:00.292 --> 00:50:01.502
[Ed sighs]

713
00:50:04.505 --> 00:50:06.006
Ah. of course not.

714
00:50:07.382 --> 00:50:10.219
[chuckles] This is
so fucking typical.

715
00:50:11.470 --> 00:50:12.720
Typical of what?

716
00:50:12.721 --> 00:50:14.097
Of you!

717
00:50:15.474 --> 00:50:19.727
Always so eager to please the
higher-ups to further your own career.

718
00:50:19.728 --> 00:50:22.022
I came out of retirement
to take this job.

719
00:50:22.523 --> 00:50:25.191
You think I give a
damn about my career?

720
00:50:25.192 --> 00:50:27.653
If this is typical
of anybody. it's you.

721
00:50:28.320 --> 00:50:29.780
What's that supposed to mean?

722
00:50:30.364 --> 00:50:34.116
Time after time. you make exceptions
for the people you care about.

723
00:50:34.117 --> 00:50:36.160
And now you're doing
it again with her.

724
00:50:36.161 --> 00:50:39.039
You don't think I see what's
going on between the two of you?

725
00:50:39.540 --> 00:50:43.084
Once again. you're letting your
personal feelings affect your judgment.

726
00:50:43.085 --> 00:50:44.168
Once again?

727
00:50:44.169 --> 00:50:47.380
Gordo on Jamestown.
Danny when we...

728
00:50:47.381 --> 00:50:49.298
Wait. whatever happened
to Danny is not on me!

729
00:50:49.299 --> 00:50:50.425
Really?

730
00:50:50.926 --> 00:50:54.137
You don't remember me pleading
with you that he wasn't ready?

731
00:50:54.638 --> 00:50:57.724
But you ignored me! Because
you didn't want to see it.

732
00:50:58.725 --> 00:51:01.687
You let your emotions get the best
of you and because of that. he...

733
00:51:04.439 --> 00:51:05.774
And because of that. what?

734
00:51:08.318 --> 00:51:09.444
Now say it. Dani.

735
00:51:10.821 --> 00:51:11.822
Say it.

736
00:51:14.616 --> 00:51:15.993
[whispering] Say it.

737
00:51:16.952 --> 00:51:20.789
Svetlana Zakharova will be on
Unity when it leaves tonight.

738
00:51:21.999 --> 00:51:24.168
My decision is made.

739
00:51:40.184 --> 00:51:41.643
[engineer speaks Russian]

740
00:51:59.494 --> 00:52:00.621
Tatyana?

741
00:52:09.171 --> 00:52:10.589
[in Russian] Are you okay?

742
00:52:15.886 --> 00:52:17.262
The KGB took him.

743
00:52:18.222 --> 00:52:19.681
Took who?

744
00:52:21.016 --> 00:52:24.019
My mentor. Kirill Semenov.

745
00:52:27.272 --> 00:52:28.814
No...

746
00:52:28.815 --> 00:52:30.483
No. that's not...

747
00:52:30.484 --> 00:52:33.528
He was fired. She wouldn't...

748
00:52:33.529 --> 00:52:35.238
Of course she would.

749
00:52:35.239 --> 00:52:36.532
She is one of them.

750
00:52:37.783 --> 00:52:40.117
Two men came to his office

751
00:52:40.118 --> 00:52:42.119
and they took him away.
in front of everyone.

752
00:52:42.120 --> 00:52:44.039
No one did a thing.

753
00:52:45.999 --> 00:52:47.834
Cowards. all of them.

754
00:52:47.835 --> 00:52:48.961
[sniffles]

755
00:52:50.337 --> 00:52:52.047
Even me.

756
00:52:53.257 --> 00:52:55.050
[sniffling]

757
00:52:59.012 --> 00:53:00.013
[speaks Russian]

758
00:53:02.641 --> 00:53:03.809
[sniffles]

759
00:53:20.450 --> 00:53:21.702
[door opens]

760
00:53:24.079 --> 00:53:25.289
Good afternoon. everyone.

761
00:53:27.916 --> 00:53:29.459
I have good news.

762
00:53:31.962 --> 00:53:33.714
The Americans have folded.

763
00:53:34.590 --> 00:53:36.716
Thanks to our efforts.

764
00:53:36.717 --> 00:53:40.720
Cosmonaut Zakharova will stand trial
for her crimes against the state.

765
00:53:40.721 --> 00:53:42.598
Great job. thank you.

766
00:53:43.140 --> 00:53:47.518
Now we have another busy
day. so let's begin.

767
00:53:47.519 --> 00:53:49.479
- [clears throat]
- [papers shuffling]

768
00:53:50.731 --> 00:53:53.775
First item on the agenda...

769
00:54:03.368 --> 00:54:04.995
[in English] This is everything.

770
00:54:06.079 --> 00:54:08.999
Hopper launch is in
30 minutes. I suppose.

771
00:54:10.334 --> 00:54:11.960
No. this isn't over.

772
00:54:12.711 --> 00:54:14.671
Uh. Sveta. you don't have to...

773
00:54:15.380 --> 00:54:18.132
If we leave now. we can
make it down to sublevel 4.

774
00:54:18.133 --> 00:54:21.677
They're still working on the east
module there and it's pressurized.

775
00:54:21.678 --> 00:54:23.221
but no one's down
there right now.

776
00:54:23.222 --> 00:54:24.305
Edward.

777
00:54:24.306 --> 00:54:27.517
I-I could bring you supplies and
food till all this blows over

778
00:54:27.518 --> 00:54:29.477
and then we figure out
how we keep you here.

779
00:54:29.478 --> 00:54:34.233
Edward. I will not let you destroy
your career to protect mine.

780
00:54:55.337 --> 00:54:56.505
[knocks]

781
00:55:05.264 --> 00:55:06.514
I'll walk her down.

782
00:55:06.515 --> 00:55:09.225
Uh. sir. Are you sure? There's
a lot of angry people out there.

783
00:55:09.226 --> 00:55:10.894
I said I'll walk her down.

784
00:55:11.520 --> 00:55:12.521
Aye. aye. sir.

785
00:55:20.070 --> 00:55:22.030
[both sigh]

786
00:55:23.907 --> 00:55:24.908
[sniffles]

787
00:55:25.868 --> 00:55:26.910
You ready?

788
00:56:40.484 --> 00:56:44.029
Goodbye. Edward.

789
00:57:20.524 --> 00:57:21.859
[sighs]
